column5: Spent the last week on the French (Totem Point Lodge...:AWESOME place).  Fishing was solid at the beginning of the week....boated over 30 walleye and then it shut down mid-week.  Got a pb 27" eye though...that thing was huge to me.  Great week...even greater scenery.  Love that area.
Good on ya! Thanks for the report.

Good to hear you had a great time on Wolseley Bay and at Totem Point. The scenery is much more intimate than the West Arm and offers a different feel, one I'm sure you noticed and enjoyed.  Now how about some photos of all those walters
